[normal]Written evidence submitted by [bold]Women’s Aid [bold]&#xa0;[bold]Summary[bold]Women's Aid is the national domestic violence charity that co-ordinates and 
[normal]supports an England-wide network of over 300 local services working to end domestic violence against women and children.
[normal] Keeping the voices of survivors at the heart of its work, Women's Aid campaigns for better legal protection and services, providing a s
[normal]trategic "expert view" to government on laws, policy and practice affecting abused women and children. In partnership with its national network, Women's Aid runs public awareness and education campaigns, bringing together national and local action, and dev
[normal]eloping new training and resources.
