[normal])
[normal] and running the Freephone 24 Hour National Domestic Violence Helpline in partne
[normal]rship with Refuge - 0808 2000 247.
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Women’s Aid welcomes the opportunity to submit written evidence to the Work and Pensions Select Committee Inquiry into support for housing costs in the reformed welfare system and will restrict comments to our areas of e
[normal]xpertise. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]This response focuses on the implications of changes for survivors of domestic violence and the t
[normal]rea
[normal]tment of housing costs within Universal Credit. 
